-v1.07 -Added support for PowerBoss external power distributors. This is in the pdNextGen object branch which also supports the internal power distributor of the SiteBoss 571. The old SNMP support for the internal power distributor is kept in the older sub-branches of the powerDistributionStatus branch (pdConfig, pdMain, pdOutput). The idea behind the pdNextGen object branch is that there are 31 items for power monitoring and alarming, and these items are organized in a double-indexed SNMP table object: the first index is for the power distributor (and has the same numbering scheme as an EventSensor -- like esIndexES, but is called pdnIndexPD), and the second index is the power output to which the item applies (or just '1' if the item is not specific to a particular power output). E.g., to read the main current of the internal power distributor, you can use the old object (pdMainCurrentValue.0) or you can use the new object (pdnMainCurrentValue.200.1). To read the fuse event state of power output number 8 on the power distributor (PowerBoss) at index 2, read pdnOutputFuseInEventState.2.8.

-v1.06 -Changed deadband, threshold, and current values for temperature sensors from integer to floating-point type. This means the SNMP object type for the temperature settings (deadbands and thresholds) changed from Integer32 to DisplayString. -Fixed bug where SNMP integer range defined in the MIB for trapIncludedValue was 16-bit instead of 32-bit.
-v1.05 -Fixed bug where some stock traps had too few varbinds declared. -Removed useless trap definitions.

-v1.04 -Removed useless object consoleInlineHsk. -Added asset management object branch. -Added altitude location object. -Removed all obsolete switch references, made everything consistent on outputs (relay outputs or power outputs). -Added threshold objects for power distribution sensors. -Added pdOutputCurrentValue object. -Fixed description for pdOutputCurrentInEventState.
